Notes.Text: These are all security issues fixed in the texlive-latex-web-companion-2021.187.svn29349-47.2 package on the GA media of openSUSE Tumbleweed.

Vulnerabilities.Description: TeX Live allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands by leveraging inclusion of mpost in shell_escape_commands in the texmf.cnf config file.
